Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 444d
Effective date: July 10th, 2019
Last updated: December 20th, 2023
This policy covers the following applications owned and operated by PIXOWL INC: The Addams Family: Mystery Mansion, Peanuts: Snoopy's Town Tale and Goosebumps: Horror Town ("the Applications").
We take your privacy seriously. This privacy statement applies only to the collection and use of information in the Applications listed. The Applications are for all ages but we are aware that some younger users may want to play and therefore we have provided a restricted version for them.
We may make changes to this policy from time to time so please be sure to check regularly. If we make a material change we will post notice prior to making the change. If we have your contact details we will contact you before we make the change.
Children's Privacy
Kids privacy assured by PRIVO: COPPA Safe Harbor Certification.
PIXOWL INC is a member of the PRIVO Kids Privacy Assured COPPA Safe Harbor Certification Program (‚Äúthe Program‚Äù).
The Program certification applies to the digital properties listed on the validation page that is viewable by clicking on the link below.
PRIVO is an independent, third-party organization committed to safeguarding children's personal information collected online. The PRIVO COPPA certification Seal posted on this page indicates PIXOWL INC has established COPPA compliant privacy practices and has agreed to submit to PRIVO‚Äôs oversight and consumer dispute resolution process.
If you have questions or concerns about our privacy practices, please contact us at (833) 807-4006 or privacy@pixowl.com. If you have further concerns after you have contacted us, you can contact PRIVO directly at
privacy@privo.com
To view the PRIVO verified page for the COPPA Safe Harbor program please visit this link:
https://cert.privo.com/#/companies/pixowl
Information we collect
The applications do not actively collect information from users 13 and under. The Application collects localization information, device model, OS version, IP address, UDID and geolocation information at country or state level. Younger users are unable to create an account or access sharing features within the Application.
Service Providers
We work with some third party service providers in relation to children 13 years of age or under. Younger users are unable to access sharing features within the Applications.
These ad networks serve contextual ads and do not share user data with any other third parties. For more information on these third party service providers, please review their privacy policies:
Ad Colony:
http://www.adcolony.com/privacy-policy
IronSource:
https://developers.ironsrc.com/ironsource-mobile/air/ironsource-mobile-privacy-policy
Unity:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
Vungle:
https://vungle.com/privacy/
We work with Crashlytics to help report bugs and game crashes. Crashlytics does not collect any custom data. For more information, please see the Crashlytics privacy policy:
http://try.crashlytics.com/terms/
We work with Google Analytics for Firebase. Google Analytics uses the data to provide analytics and attribution information. The precise information collected can vary by device and environment. An IP address, to determine a user‚Äôs country, and non-personal usage data is collected for users aged 13 and under in the US. For more information, please check Firebase's privacy policy:
https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
We work with Helpshift for customer support. We use the enableFullPrivacy flag to ensure that personal information is not collected through the Helpshift dashboard. For more information, please review Helpshift‚Äôs privacy policy:
https://www.helpshift.com/privacypolicy/
We work with IAB Open Measurement for Ad quality measurement, ad analytics, ad fraud prevention and quality control. IAB Open Measurement does not collect personal information.
If you have any questions about our children‚Äôs privacy policy please email us at:
privacy@pixowl.com
