Disclosure
PIXOWL may disclose personal information only if required by law or in case there is the firm belief that such action is necessary to:
Comply with laws and local regulations.
Protect and defend the rights or property of the Application and PIXOWL INC.
In the event that the company is merged or sold.
Links
We may include links to third parties from the website or services. We aren‚Äôt responsible for these companies and because we have a link doesn‚Äôt mean we endorse them.
Your use of our services may be subject to the terms and conditions and privacy policies of other services that we don‚Äôt control such as mobile app stores, mobile software platforms or payment processors.
Please be sure to check their privacy policies if you decide to visit them.
Security
The Applications use generally accepted security measures and safeguards in an attempt to keep the data it collects secure and requires that the third parties it works with agree to do the same. The measures and safeguards include limiting access to the data to those persons who need it to complete their work for the Applications and using a fire-wall protected environment and storing personal information in secure operating environments.
Please be aware though that, despite our best efforts, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable.
